SIMPLE: pseudo
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pseudo-
<hw>Pseu"do-</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[Gr. <grk>pseydh`s</grk> lying,
false, akin to <grk>psey`dein</grk> to belie; cf. <grk>psydro`s</grk>
lying, <grk>psy`qos</grk> a lie.]</ety> <def>A combining form or prefix
signifying <xex>false</xex>, <xex>counterfeit</xex>,
<xex>pretended</xex>, <xex>spurious</xex>; <as>as,
<ex>pseudo</ex>-apostle, a false apostle; <ex>pseudo</ex>-clergy, false
or spurious clergy; <ex>pseudo</ex>-episcopacy, <ex>pseudo</ex>-form,
<ex>pseudo</ex>-martyr, <ex>pseudo</ex>-philosopher</as>. Also used
adjectively.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pseudobacteria</ent>⟦br⟧
